        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1811344078" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8814278467609639287">The Law is never perfect. It&apos;s development is always detrmined by the thinking of the time. Once a principle is considered inapplicable at a certain stage of life, the experts are normally called in to give an opinion as to the relevance of it. This was the case when Gideon filed a motion at the United States Supreme Court arguing that his rights was infringed by a Florida court when he was denied Counsel during his criminal trial. <br/><br/>Abe Fortas, acting for Gideon had to translate his arguments int</span>
  <span id="freeText8814278467609639287" style="display:none">The Law is never perfect. It's development is always detrmined by the thinking of the time. Once a principle is considered inapplicable at a certain stage of life, the experts are normally called in to give an opinion as to the relevance of it. This was the case when Gideon filed a motion at the United States Supreme Court arguing that his rights was infringed by a Florida court when he was denied Counsel during his criminal trial. <br /><br />Abe Fortas, acting for Gideon had to translate his arguments into the technical legal language required by law. He acted for him in the Supreme Court, having been appointed by the Judges at the time. He was a successful advocated. The State of Florida was represented by the Assistant attorney general Jacob Brown, who later went into private practice. Twenty three states appeared as friends of the court, buy argued for the overulling of Bretts vs. Brady. Only two states argued for the retention of the verdict. <br /><br />The court unanimously ruled in favor of a depature from the rule in Bretts vs. Brady. What remained is the practicality of having counsel in every criminal case a person faces. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8814278467609639287" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

