        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1700059718" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16093042462284500293">Of course I&apos;ve known about Gideon vs. Wainwright since I was in high school in the 1960s, and I studied the case in law school and taught it in my Constitution and Law class - but I had never read Anthony Lewis&apos; classic until now. In language that any reader can readily grasp, he not only paints a portrait of Gideon, the real human being whose criminal conviction was overturned, but he also provides an elegant perspective on the historical and legal evolution of the Supreme Court&apos;s thinking on t</span>
  <span id="freeText16093042462284500293" style="display:none">Of course I've known about Gideon vs. Wainwright since I was in high school in the 1960s, and I studied the case in law school and taught it in my Constitution and Law class - but I had never read Anthony Lewis' classic until now. In language that any reader can readily grasp, he not only paints a portrait of Gideon, the real human being whose criminal conviction was overturned, but he also provides an elegant perspective on the historical and legal evolution of the Supreme Court's thinking on the subject of a criminal defendant's right to counsel. Lewis also provides an excellent historical perspective on the developing role of the Supreme Court in our systems of government - both federal and state. A very good book for high school civics classrooms.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16093042462284500293" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


