<div id="review_43573813" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/43573813" />
    <a title="Stefani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/123648-stefani"><img alt="Stefani" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1181540307p2/123648.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/43573813?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stefani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stefani" href="/user/show/123648-stefani">Stefani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/123648-stefani?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer43573813" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5721480669141548809">The first book I have read for law school since A Civil Action in 1L that wasn&apos;t a case book or supplement.<br/><br/>Whew. Law school should require more books like this. It is the story of how the right to representation for the indigent in all criminal cases was codified by the Supreme Court.<br/><br/>Somewhat uplifting, somewhat depressing.</span>
  <span id="freeText5721480669141548809" style="display:none">The first book I have read for law school since A Civil Action in 1L that wasn't a case book or supplement.<br /><br />Whew. Law school should require more books like this. It is the story of how the right to representation for the indigent in all criminal cases was codified by the Supreme Court.<br /><br />Somewhat uplifting, somewhat depressing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5721480669141548809" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
